rd":"Brentwood North","seats":1,"turnout_pct":44.74,"results_url":"https://brentwood.moderngov.co.uk/mgElectionElectionAreaResults.aspx?Page=all&EID=14","candidates":[{"n":"Steve Mayo","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":1017,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","inc":true,"pid":"97109"},{"n":"John Henry Roberts","p":"Reform UK","v":681,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127081","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127081/5e2969bd-1662-42fb-ad0c-30de584a7f98.png"},{"n":"John Anthony Michael Parrish","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":256,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"109744"},{"n":"John Michael Hamilton","p":"Green Party","v":198,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"11360","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/11360/c3a9b52c-0705-442e-a98e-ef28bb2543d6.png","stmt":"If there is one positive the Coronavirus has taught us, it is this: caring, vibrant, local community life is essential; essential for our quality of life and, at times, essential for our very survival.\r\n\r\nThe importance of community was clear throughout my 45-year career in education, and it could not be clearer during this global epidemic.\r\n\r\nI have lived in Brentwood for more than 33 years and the town has everything going for it.\r\n\r\nThere are parks, woodland and open spaces within minutes of the High Street. It has history as a route centre since the days of the Romans and the Pilgrims, and is within easy reach of London and the coast. Greens want to revive communities like ours. Give Greens the chance!"},{"n":"Joanna Moncrieff","p":"Labour","v":109,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"77547","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/77547/000aa69d-ac9f-4b1d-8ddb-0bb3404afe38.png"}],"female_count":1,"male_count":4,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":1,"inc_elected":1,"in