rl":"https://brentwood.moderngov.co.uk/mgElectionElectionAreaResults.aspx?Page=all&EID=14","candidates":[{"n":"Craig Thomson","p":"Reform UK","v":1240,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127119","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127119/7f737549-ff72-4517-82ff-2c9b0274bf40.png"},{"n":"Soni Parvinder Sunger","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":604,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"109859","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/109859/55a9035d-9961-4c14-80d1-c4a37d210aa9.png"},{"n":"John Maynard Chapple","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":246,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"109609"},{"n":"Rebecca Catherine Enifer","p":"Green Party","v":134,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"109543","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/109543/2dc98837-0c33-4219-b287-b03b1f075af5.png"},{"n":"Simon Ball","p":"Labour","v":103,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127118"}],"female_count":2,"male_count":3,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Herongate, Ingrave & West Horndon","seats":1,"turnout_pct":51.23,"results_url":"https://brentwood.moderngov.co.uk/mgElectionElectionAreaResults.aspx?Page=all&EID=14","candidates":[{"n":"Omar Bakhsh","p":"Reform UK","v":828,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"127108","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127108/5f8a537f-a933-40ee-94f3-8ac42a2be62b.png"},{"n":"Sim Owolabi","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":465,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"low","pid":"12907","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/12907/c64c79d5-201a-4529-bacc-c55e71e07197.png"},{"n":"Fiona Elizabeth Marsh","p":"Independent","v":228,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"98104","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/98104/cc879d7e-adf6-4d46-913c-ceeb384cdd12.png"},{"n":"Gary Maxius","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":122,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"109657"},{"n":"Charlotte Bradford","p":"Green Party","v":98,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127109","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127109/2fcf5256-60ac-4d64-82ee-c94b9debd445.png"},{"n":"Kevin Brailey","p":"Labour","v":58,"r":6,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"77533"}],"female_count":2,"male_count":4,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Hutton East","seats":1,"turnout_pct":48.4,"results_url":"https://brentwood.moderngov.co.uk/mgElectionElectionAreaResults.aspx?Page=all&EID=14","candidates":[{"n":"Paul Nicholas Godfrey","p":"Reform UK","v":800,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"98111","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/98111/f6d6c265-aba9-4081-a718-e03daccc4464.png","stmt":"I have lived in Brentwood most of my life, having moved here with my parents as a very young child\n\nI have always voted, but over the last few years I have become increasingly disillusioned with the incompetence, lies, and broken promises of the prevailing government, and the current party of opposition just offers more of the same. Britain deserves better. Reform UK offer a proper genuine alternative to the current two-party system.\n\nI believe that Britain cannot sustain the massive immigration numbers that we have seen over the last few years. I believe that the race towards net zero is hitting the poorest in society first and ultimately will lead to us all being colder and poorer. I believe in a low regulation low taxation economy that encourages free market economics, in a society where the rights of criminals do not trump the rights of victims, and where children should be protected and the elderly respected.\n\nWe managed to find £37 billion to pay for a failed test track and trace system during Covid, yet fail to adequately fund our NHS, Social Care, Education or Criminal Justice system. Taxation is the highest it has been in over 70 years, and government overreach is out of control. This is all wrong. Westminster seems to have forgotten that the government exists because of the people; the people do not exist because of the government.\n\nWhen I discovered Reform UK, I found a party that shared many of my views. Standing as a political candidate was never on my “to do” list, but circumstances change.\n\nI applied and was accepted to stand for Reform UK at the next General Election, giving the people of Brentwood and Ongar an alternative to the current two-party system. It’s time for people to stop voting for the least worst option, and start voting for what they believe in.","tw":"\"paulngodfrey\""},{"n":"Thomas John Bridge","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":706,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"12887","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/12887/586affe4-75ae-4053-846d-9801f700871c.png","stmt":"Dear Hutton South Resident,\n\nWith the sad passing of our dear friend and colleague Cllr Mark Reed we lost a local community councillor who many local people (whatever their politics) hugely admired for his hard-work and personality.  This by-election, vote to elect someone who will also put local people first in everything that they do.\n\nI am honoured to be chosen as Conservative Candidate, as Mark was such a well respected figure locally and I want to carry on his legacy.  I have served as a Brentwood councillor previously so I know what needs to be done to help you with queries and problems that you might have.\n\nIf you are anything like me, you’ll be seriously frustrated by what has being going on in national politics.  Frankly, no political party has covered themselves in glory over the last few years.  So I completely understand the temptation of not voting or perhaps to cast a protest vote.  This election locally isn’t going to change what’s happening in Westminster, despite what some parties might say on their leaflets.  This election is about what happens locally here in Hutton and Brentwood.  Whilst some prefer to focus on national politics I am focused on LOCAL issues that matter to LOCAL people here :\n\n✅ Protect our Greenbelt and oppose inappropriate development\n \nWe are lucky that Brentwood has beautiful countryside and green spaces.  But with increased mandatory housing targets imposed by the Labour Government it is important that we do not see these destroyed. New housing should be in the right location and with the right infrastructure provided. I will fight to make sure that the interests of local people are considered and that natural habitats such as Hare Hall Shaw and Mosbach Pond are protected for future generations.\n\nAt the end of last year an expression of interest in a New Town was sent  by our LibDem/Labour jointly run Borough Council.  Conservative Councillors opposed this due to the lack of any public debate or scrutiny.  Sadly Labour and th","tw":"\"thomasbridge\""},{"n":"Nina Allan","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":470,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127115"},{"n":"Jamie Daniel Miller","p":"Green Party","v":144,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"127116","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127116/9124d8ab-9e83-4317-8f8e-53f77f452409.png"},{"n":"Richard Millwood","p":"Labour","v":100,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"12896","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/12896.png","stmt":"Richard has lived and worked in Brentwood since 1990 in the local university and as governor for two schools. He acts as a consultant on education and technology as well as leading research in the field. His concerns are that education is badly underfunded, that it should have democratic overview and that the academy and free school arrangements have lead to overpaid chief executives of unaccountable trusts. This affects local residents by making it easy for schools to drop support for a wide curriculum, leaving out the creative subjects and opportunities for children with special needs.\r\n\r\nIf elected Richard  will work hard to sort out the housing crisis in Brentwood, which leaves many young people unable to afford a home and will pursue education issues working with the County Council.","tw":"\"richardmillwood\""}],"female_count":1,"male_count":4,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Hutton North","seats":1,"turnout_pct":47.96,"results_url":"https://brentwood.moderngov.co.uk/mgElectionElectionAreaResults.aspx?Page=all&EID=14","candidates":[{"n":"Jay Patel","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":903,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","inc":true,"pid":"92099","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/92099/3311f287-5bae-49b6-82f7-96006b6c12d3.png"},{"n":"Chris Hossack","p":"Reform UK","v":769,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"127123","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127123/4ff7359d-e7d5-4e94-9d68-1e634cab94a1.png"},{"n":"Adam Hoxha","p":"Green Party","v":197,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127124","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127124/d75ee617-9835-496f-ba4a-5b71176dba58.png"},{"n":"Nita Jhummu","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":189,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127125"},{"n":"Phil Holland","p":"Labour","v":146,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"77542"}],"female_count":1,"male_count":4,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":1,"inc_elected":1,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":0},{"ward":"Hutton South","seats":1,"turnout_pct":46.47,"results_url":"https://brentwood.moderngov.co.uk/mgElectionAreaResults.aspx?ID=105&RPID=61690074","candidates":[{"n":"Philippa Ruth Nicholson","p":"Reform UK","v":987,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127127","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127127/f3611e65-9d64-46aa-a249-26af98bd21f5.png"},{"n":"Mellissa Mary Slade","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":785,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"high","inc":true,"pid":"62249","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/62249/73eec616-ad68-4572-97e2-9bc4060fe7da.png"},{"n":"Heather Margaret Leathley","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":302,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"109852"},{"n":"David Mark Hale","p":"Green Party","v":186,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"96400","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/96400/4ae35a05-15d0-4a9f-b678-3bad540a24e8.png"},{"n":"Jane Winter","p":"Labour","v":165,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"12890","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/12890/736fc905-a1d2-4621-a607-3d0ccbe142ec.png","stmt":"Jane is a long term Brentwood Borough resident, having moved here in 1972.  She worked for the NHS for over 40 years and is determined to see health and social care meeting residents’ needs effectively. A believer in community-led working she is a Parish Councillor in Ingatestone & Fryerning, where she lives, leading on the production of a Neighbourhood Plan.\n\nIf elected she will strive for a decent standard of living for all working age people. She will make it a priority that the Local and County Council pay it’s directly managed staff a Living Wage and include this clause in all of its contracted service providers.\n\nShe will actively support apprenticeship schemes within the Borough and Parish Councils and community services for local young people, working with the County Council to achieve this. She will work with the local Community Policing Team to understand residents’ issues and work towards a safer Ward."}],"female_count":4,"male_count":1,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":1,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":1,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Ingatestone, Fryerning & Mountnessing","seats":1,"turnout_pct":51.49,"results_url":"https://brentwood.moderngov.co.uk/mgElectionElectionAreaResults.aspx?Page=all&EID=14","candidates":[{"n":"Lesley Anne Wagland","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":930,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","inc":true,"pid":"29726","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/29726-2400591a-3538-4696-a622-42adf21e3977.png"},{"n":"Martin Paul Lonergan","p":"Reform UK","v":814,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127157"},{"n":"Louise Susann Donno","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":645,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127156","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127156/25057e29-a7c5-431c-8f24-f96852471b22.png"},{"n":"Paul Francis Jeater","p":"Green Party","v":161,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"4658","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/4658.png","stmt":"I moved to Ingatestone 30 years ago and taught in a secondary school in Brentwood for 20 years. As a Parish Councillor I am heavily involved in my local community and this involvement also extends to being Chair of Ingatestone & Fryerning Cricket Club.\n\nI joined the Green Party in 2011 and was selected to be our parliamentary candidate in Brentwood in both 2017 and 2019 general elections.\n\nThe last year has shown the vital importance of local communities. We are fortunate to have access to green space, but it must be defended against unsustainable development.\n\nBoth Brentwood and Essex councils need Green councillors to raise the issues that other parties often ignore. The climate and ecological crisis that we face needs addressing without delay - a vote for the Green Party is a vote for climate action now.","tw":"\"EssexWomble\""},{"n":"Caroline Russell","p":"Labour","v":41,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"109823"}],"female_count":3,"male_count":2,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":1,"inc_elected":1,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":0},{"ward":"Pilgrims Hatch","seats":1,"turnout_pct":46.62,"results_url":"https://brentwood.moderngov.co.uk/mgElectionElectionAreaResults.aspx?Page=all&EID=14","candidates":[{"n":"Samuel John Gascoyne","p":"Reform UK","v":993,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127130","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127130/d0846eea-a9e7-44ea-aef6-deee2fabb9b2.png"},{"n":"Mark Robert Lewis","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":821,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"41863","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/41863-32ab13b6-a18d-453b-9801-5f96efc524a1.png","url":"\"https://brentwoodlibdems.org.uk/en/\"","bd":"1961"},{"n":"Gordon William Frank Cowley","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":192,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"12899","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/12899/3ab10c2c-0220-4626-a5fe-2d6162cba0d5.png"},{"n":"Dom Graham","p":"Green Party","v":108,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"127131"},{"n":"Ankie Saunders","p":"Labour","v":68,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"127132"}],"female_count":1,"male_count":4,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Shenfield","seats":1,"turnout_pct":56.79,"results_url":"https://brentwood.moderngov.co.uk/mgElectionElectionAreaResults.aspx?Pa